<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The total amount of unrecognized tax benefits excluding interest and penalties that, if recognized, would affect the effective tax rate as of September&#160;30, 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively, are $1.2 million, $0.9&#160;million and $1.0&#160;million. Currently, the Company does not expect the liability for unrecognized tax benefits to change significantly in the next 12 months and has classified the above balances on the consolidated balance sheets in other long-term liabilities. Interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits are recorded in income tax expense. As of September&#160;30, 2016, 2015 and 2014, a gross balance of $0.6&#160;million, $0.6&#160;million and $0.7&#160;million, respectively, has been accrued related to the unrecognized tax benefits balance for interest and penalties.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Company files income tax returns, including returns for its subsidiaries, in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and in various state jurisdictions as well as several non-U.S. jurisdictions. Uncertain tax positions are related to tax years that remain subject to examination. The Internal Revenue Service (&#8220;IRS&#8221;) completed an examination of the Company&#8217;s U.S. income tax return for fiscal 2012 in the fourth quarter of fiscal 2014 with a payment made associated with a timing adjustment. U.S. income tax returns for years prior to fiscal 2013 are no longer subject to examination by federal tax authorities. For tax returns for state and local jurisdictions, the Company is no longer subject to examination for tax years generally before fiscal 2006. For tax returns for non-U.S. jurisdictions, the Company is no longer subject to income tax examination for years prior to 2011. Additionally, the Company has been indemnified of liability for any taxes relating to Creagh Medical and NorMedix for periods prior to the respective acquisition dates, pursuant to the terms of the related share purchase agreements. As of September 30, 2016 and 2015 there were no undistributed earnings in foreign subsidiaries.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	F-29
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage82"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU77">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	9.&#160;&#160;Defined Contribution Pl
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	an
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Company has a 401(k) retirement and savings plan for the benefit of qualifying U.S. employees. The Company matches 50% of employee contributions on the first 6% of eligible compensation. Company contributions totaling $0.3 million, $0.3&#160;million and $0.2 million have been expensed in the years ended September&#160;30, 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	10.&#160;&#160;Amounts Reclassified Out of Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Amounts reclassified out of Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income (&#8220;AOCI&#8221;) totaled $0.3 and $0.1 million on a pre-tax basis for the fiscal year ended September 30, 2015 and 2014, respectively. There were no amounts reclassified out of AOCI for fiscal 2016. The amounts reclassified out of AOCI for fiscal 2015 were associated with unrealized gains on available-for-sale securities that were realized on the sale of the securities and are presented in other income, net in the consolidated statements of income.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	11.&#160;&#160;Commitments and Contingencies
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:5%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Litigation.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	&#160;From time to time, the Company has been, and may become, involved in various legal actions involving its operations, products and technologies, including intellectual property and employment disputes. The outcomes of these legal actions are not within the Company&#8217;s complete control and may not be known for prolonged periods of time. In some actions, the claimants seek damages as well as other relief, including injunctions barring the sale of products that are the subject of the lawsuit, which if granted, could require significant expenditures or result in lost revenue. The Company records a liability in the consolidated financial statements for these actions when a loss is known or considered probable and the amount can be reasonably estimated. If the reasonable estimate of a known or probable loss is a range, and no amount within the range is a better estimate, the minimum amount of the range is accrued. If a loss is possible but not known or probable, and can be reasonably estimated, the estimated loss or range of loss is disclosed. In most cases, significant judgment is required to estimate the amount and timing of a loss to be recorded.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the Company&#8217;s Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q for the periods ended March&#160;31, 2015, and June&#160;30, 2015, it was disclosed a notice was received from a customer alleging an overpayment of approximately $5.7 million in royalties covering the period January 2009 through September 2014 (the &#8220;Claim&#8221;). On September&#160;29, 2015, the Company entered into a settlement and release agreement resolving the Claim. Under the agreement, among other things, (a)&#160;the Company agreed to pay the customer $2.5 million to settle the Claim, (b)&#160;the customer agreed to pay the Company approximately $0.5 million for undisputed royalties that were unpaid and were not previously recognized, during fiscal 2015, and (c)&#160;the Company and the customer agreed to a mutual release relating to the Claim and certain other claims by the Company for royalties owed by the customer. In connection with the settlement, in the fourth quarter of fiscal 2015, the Company recognized revenue of approximately $0.5 million and recorded a charge of approximately $2.5 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	InnoRx, Inc.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	In January 2005, the Company entered into a merger agreement whereby the Company acquired all of the assets of InnoRx, Inc. (&#8220;InnoRx&#8221;), an early stage company developing drug delivery devices and therapies for the ophthalmology market. The Company will be required to issue up to approximately 480,059 additional shares of its common stock to the stockholders of InnoRx upon the successful completion of the remaining development and commercial milestones involving InnoRx technology acquired in the transaction. The Company has not recorded any accrual for this contingency as of September 30, 2016 as the milestones have not been achieved and the probability of achievement is remote.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	InnoCore Technologies BV.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	&#160;In March 2006, the Company entered into a license agreement whereby Surmodics obtained an exclusive license to a drug delivery coating for licensed products within the vascular field which included peripheral, coronary and neurovascular biodurable stent product. The license requires an annual minimum payment of 200,000 euros (equivalent to $224,000 using a euro to US $ exchange rate of 1.1222 as of September 30, 2016) until the last patent expires which is currently estimated to be September 2027. The total minimum future payments associated with this license are approximately $2.7 million. The license is currently utilized with one of Surmodics&#8217; drug delivery customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU78">
</A>
	PR Pharmaceuticals, Inc.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	In November 2008, SurModics Pharmaceuticals acquired certain contracts and assets of PR Pharma to enhance its portfolio of drug delivery technologies for the pharmaceutical and biotechnology industries. The Company agreed to indemnify Evonik, for a period of five years, for up to $2.5 million of contingent consideration obligations owed to the sellers of PR Pharma related to a future patent issuance milestone when it sold substantially all of the SurModics Pharmaceuticals assets to Evonik on November 17, 2011. In the fourth quarter of fiscal 2014, Surmodics submitted a bid of less than $0.1 million related to the Company&#8217;s indemnification obligations to Evonik related to a contingent consideration matter associated with the PR Pharma
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	F-30
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage83"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	intellectual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	property purchased by Evonik in the Pharma Sale. Surmodics was notified in October 2014 that the bid was accepted with a payment made at that time. The indemnification period expired on November 17, 2016 with no additional claims.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Operating Leases.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	&#160;The Company leases certain facilities under noncancelable operating lease agreements. Rent expense for the years ended September&#160;30, 2016, 2015 and 2014 was $0.1&#160;million for each period. Annual commitments pursuant to operating lease agreements are as follows
</FONT>
	(in thousands):

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	12.&#160;&#160;Reportable Segment Information
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The accounting standards for reporting information about operating segments define operating segments as components of an enterprise about which separate financial information is available that is evaluated regularly by the chief operating decision maker, who is the Company&#8217;s Chief Executive Officer, in deciding how to allocate resources and in assessing performance. For financial accounting and reporting purposes, the Company reports its results for the two reportable segments as follows: (1)&#160;the Medical Device unit, which is comprised of surface modification coating technologies to improve access, deliverability, and predictable deployment of medical devices; international cardiology and peripheral balloon design, development and manufacturing; as well as drug delivery coating technologies to provide site-specific drug delivery from the surface of a medical device, with end markets that include coronary, peripheral, neuro-vascular and urology, among others, and (2) the In Vitro Diagnostics unit, which consists of component products and technologies for diagnostic test kits and biomedical research applications, with products that include protein stabilization reagents, substrates, antigens and surface coatings. During fiscal 2016, the Company acquired Creagh Medical and NorMedix, which are included in the Medical Device segment.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The tables below present segment revenue, operating income from continuing operations and depreciation and amortization, for the years ended September&#160;30, as follows (in thousands):
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU79">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Corporate category includes expenses that are not fully allocated to Medical Device and In Vitro Diagnostics segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;These Corporate costs are related to functions, such as executive management, corporate accounting, leg
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	al, human resources and Board of Directors. Corporate may also include expenses, such as litigation, which are not specific to a segment and thus not allocated to the operating segments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Corporate segment results above for fiscal 2014 include increased stock option expense of $0.9 million related to a modification of equity awards granted to Board members.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Asset information by segment is not presented because the Company does not provide its chief operating decision maker assets by segment, as the data is not readily available.
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the first quarter of fiscal 2016, the Company recorded expense related to acquisition related costs, including due diligence and integration expenses of $2.5 million, related to the acquisitions of Creagh Medical and NorMedix (Note 3).
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	During the second quarter of fiscal 2016, the Company recorded an out-of-period adjustment of $1.1 million to correct a cumulative overstatement of royalty revenue, of which $1.0 million related to years prior to fiscal 2016. The overstatement was evaluated and concluded to not be material to fiscal 2016, or any prior interim or annual periods.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the third quarter of fiscal 2016, the Company recorded a $2.9 million customer royalty catch-up payment related to periods prior to the third quarter fiscal 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the fourth quarter of fiscal 2016, the Company recorded a $0.5 million reduction of the income tax provision related to the adoption of ASU 2016-09 as discussed in Note 2.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the fourth quarter of fiscal 2015, the Company recorded expense related to the settlement of a claim of $2.5 million, a $1.5 million impairment loss on a strategic investment and recognized $0.8 million in previously contingent royalties.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the third quarter of fiscal 2015, the Company recorded a $0.6 million customer royalty catch-up payment related to periods prior to the third quarter fiscal 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:3.33%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-10K_20160930_HTM_NOTES_TO_CONS_FINANCIAL_STATEMENTS_END">
</A>
<A NAME="SRDX-10K_20160930_HTM_NOTES_TO_CONS_FINANCIAL_STATEMENTS_END">
</A>
	In the second quarter of fiscal 2015, the Company recorded a $0.5 million gain on a strategic investment in Intersect ENT shares.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-TOP:3PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Exhibit 10.18
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:3PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/02/0001564590-16-029755_G2016120218593957210656.JPG" TITLE="" ALT="" STYLE="WIDTH:192PX;HEIGHT:24PX;">
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Board Compensation Policy
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Surmodics, Inc.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:3PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(Approved: April 26, 2016)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:24PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Directors of Surmodics, Inc. (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Company
</FONT>
	&#8221;) that are not employed by the Company (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	non-employee directors
</FONT>
	&#8221;) are entitled to the compensation set forth below for their service as a member of the Board of Directors (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Board
</FONT>
	&#8221;) of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board reserves the right to amend this policy from time to time.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:3PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	A.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cash Compensation
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Beginning in fiscal 2016, each non-employee director of the Company will be entitled to receive annual cash retainers as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:18PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/02/0001564590-16-029755_G2016120218593957610656.JPG" TITLE="" ALT="" STYLE="WIDTH:321PX;HEIGHT:61PX;">
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:18PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/02/0001564590-16-029755_G2016120218593957810657.JPG" TITLE="" ALT="" STYLE="WIDTH:410PX;HEIGHT:101PX;">
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The cash retainers set forth above will become payable quarterly in arrears on the first trading day of each calendar quarter.&nbsp;&nbsp;The annual cash retainer shall be reduced by 25% if a non-employee director does not attend at least 75% of the total meetings of the Board and Board committees on which such director served during the applicable fiscal year.&nbsp;&nbsp;If, for any reason, a director does not serve an entire calendar quarter, the cash retainers will be pro-rated based on such director&#8217;s length of service during such calendar quarter.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	B.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Equity Compensation
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to the cash compensation described above, each non-employee director will also receive the following equity grants:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Initial Grant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	:&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon his or her initial election or appointment to the Board, each non-employee director will be awarded an equity grant having a value of $60,000, one-half of such award shall be in the form of a nonqualified stock option to purchase shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock (&#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Stock Options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#8221;) and the other half shall be in the form of restricted stock units (&#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	RSUs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#8221;).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-EX1018_389_HTM_OLE_LINK2">
</A>
	2.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Annual Grant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
<A NAME="SRDX-EX1018_389_HTM_OLE_LINK2">
</A>
	:&nbsp;&nbsp;On the date of the Company&#8217;s annual meeting of shareholders during each fiscal year, each non-employee director will be awarded an equity grant having a value of $60,000, one-half of such award shall be in the form of Stock Options and the other half shall be in the form of RSUs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The value of the first annual equity grant following a director&#8217;s initial election or appointment to the Board will be pro-rated based on such director&#8217;s length of service on the Board during the preceding 12-month period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="SRDX-EX1018_389_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU2">
</A>
	C.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Stock in Lieu of Cash
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;A non-employee director may elect, in a form and in a manner prescribed by the Company, to receive all or a portion of their cash retainers (&#8220;Deferred Retainers&#8221;) in the form of RSUs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such RSU award will be granted on the last trading day of the calendar quarter for which the applicable Deferred Retainers would have otherwise been paid, and the number of RSUs covered by such award will be determined using the fair market value of the Company&#8217;s common stock (i.e., the closing price) on such date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such RSUs will be fully vested as of the date of grant and will be paid in shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock on a one-for-one basis upon the termination of the director&#8217;s service on the Board (or, if earlier
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage87"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Surmodics, Inc.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Board Compensation Policy (continued)
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Page 2 of 2
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	and as permitted under applicable tax law, upon the occurrence of a change in control event).&nbsp;&nbsp;Any such election to receive an equity award in lieu of cash retainers must be made prior to the December 31 that precedes the calendar year during which the Deferred Retainers are earned by the non-employee director (or such earlier date as may be prescribed by the Company).&nbsp;&nbsp;A newly appointed or elected non-employee director may make such an election to receive an equity award in lieu of cash retainers at any time within 30 days after the director&#8217;s initial election or appointment to the Board, and such election will be effective for the first quarter following the quarter in which the election is received by the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	D.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Expense Reimbursement
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;All non-employee directors will be entitled to reimbursement from the Company for their reasonable travel and other expenses incurred in connection with attending Board or committee meetings.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.25%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	E.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	General Provisions
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;All equity awards provided pursuant to this policy shall be granted under the Company&#8217;s 2009 Equity Incentive Plan or any successor plan designated by the Board (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Plan
</FONT>
	&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The terms below shall apply to all equity awards granted on or after February 17, 2014, and all such awards shall be evidenced by, and subject to the terms and conditions set forth in, a written agreement in substantially the form approved by the Board.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Stock Options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of Stock Options granted will be determined using the Company&#8217;s Black-Scholes valuation methodology as of the date of grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Stock Option grant will (a)&#160;have a seven-year term, (b) vest ratably on a monthly basis and will become fully vested upon the earlier of (i) the 12-month anniversary of the grant date, or (ii) the date of the next year&#8217;s annual meeting, and (c) have an exercise price equal to the fair market value of the Company&#8217;s common stock on the date of grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Restricted Stock Units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of RSUs granted will be determined using the fair market value of the Company&#8217;s common stock (i.e., the closing price) on the date of grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each RSU grant will vest ratably on a monthly basis and will become fully vested on the first anniversary of the date of grant (except for RSUs granted in lieu of cash compensation which shall be fully vested as of the date of grant).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Dividend Equivalents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent the Company pays a dividend, each non-employee director shall have the right to receive dividend equivalents for each RSU held by such director on the record date for the payment of such dividend.&nbsp;&nbsp;The dividend equivalents shall be treated as reinvested in an additional number of RSUs which will be determined by dividing (a) the cash amount of any such dividend that would have been paid if the RSUs held by the director were outstanding shares of Company stock by (b) the fair market value of the Company&#8217;s common stock (i.e., the closing price) on the applicable dividend payment date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Stock Ownership Guidelines
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs shall be considered owned, but only the extent vested, for purposes of the Company&#8217;s stock ownership guidelines applicable to non-employee directors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:14.49%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:90PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Effect of Termination of Service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event the director&#8217;s service on the Board terminates for any reason, (a) all outstanding and unvested Stock Options or RSUs shall expire and be canceled, (b) except as set forth below, all vested Stock Options shall remain exercisable for up to three months after the date of such termination of service, but not later than the date the option expires, and (c) all vested RSUs shall be settled in shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock on a one-for-one basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that the director&#8217;s service on the Board terminates as a result of a disability or death, the director&#8217;s guardian or legal representative may exercise the options not later than the earlier of the date the options expire or six months after the date that the director&#8217;s service ceases by reason of such disability or death.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</EFX_EXHIBIT_10>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

	2014

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;WIDTH:1%; BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID 0.75PT TRANSPARENT;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

	The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and we have:
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.67%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.67%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b) Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.67%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.67%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d) Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</P>

	(b) Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
